Reasoning: The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the induced Erd\H{o}s-P\'osa property of subdivisions of graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves constructions and algorithms for identifying necessary conditions, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses packing and covering induced subdivisions, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC).
